"{\"Course Name\": \"SERIOUS AND APPLIED GAMES\", \"Course Level\": \"5500\", \"Dept Abbreviation\": \"IMGD\", \"Course Description\": \"This course covers methods and analysis for designing, implementing, and assessing games in serious, applied contexts. Often called \\u201cserious games\\u201d or \\u201capplied games\\u201d, these are game-based media that teach, engage with social issues, aim to increase empathy, or affect behavioral change. Students will read contemporary literature in the field of serious and applied games, design and implement their own games, and measure the effectiveness of those games in achieving educational or motivational goals.\\r\\n\", \"Requirements\": [], \"Is Cat 1\": true, \"Start Year For Cat 2\": -1}"